This paper discusses machine learning techniques for unsupervised domain adaptation, which involves transferring knowledge from a labeled domain to an unlabeled one. The paper specifically focuses on combining two popular approaches, domain confusion and self-ensembling, to learn invariant representations. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), and neural networks (cs.NE). However, given the emphasis on machine learning and computer vision in the paper, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.AI, cs.CL, and cs.NE.
